<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hannawald Wins Four Hills Ski Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- German Sven Hannawald won the
Four Hills ski jumping competition in Bischofshofen, Austria on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hannawald jumped 124 meters and 123m with his two efforts to
finish first with 247.6 points.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Hansjorg Jaekle was a surprise second on 235.2
points after jumps of 119.5 and 122 with Finland's Janne Ahonen
third on 232.7 points (118/121).
</P>
<P>
Japan's Kazuyoshi Funaki was attempting to become the first man
in history to win each of the Four Hills competitions, but
finished well down after a disappointing second jump. The
22-year-old had a final points tally of 218.9.
</P>
<P>
Funaki had the satisfaction of becoming the first Japanese
jumper to carry off the overall Four Hills title after his wins in
Germany at Obersdorf on December 29 and Garmisch-Partenkirchen on
New Year's Day, and in Austria at Innsbruck on January 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
