<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Traffic Accident Occurs near Estcourt, S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was
killed and 47 others injured today when a bus overturned on a
highway between Estcourt and the Mooi River, about 150 km
northwest of Durban, police said.
</P>
<P>
The more seriously injured persons were immediately carried by
helicopter to a hospital in Pietermaritzburg, a major city in
Kwazulu Natal Province, and the less seriously injured were taken
by ambulance to Estcourt provincial hospital.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
The highway leading to the port city of Durban is code-named
N3. It is one of the busiest national-class roads in South
Africa. It is also a road, on which major traffic accidents often
occur. 
</P>
</TEXT>
