<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Top Leader Vows to Continue Renovation Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party chief
Le Kha Phieu said the only chance for Vietnam to develop is the
continuation of its renovation policy "along the socialist line."
</P>
<P>
Le Kha Phieu, elected the party general secretary in December
last year, made the remarks in an interview published Tuesday by
the Vietnam news agency.
</P>
<P>
"The latest changes in the highest level of the party hierarchy
were effected with a high degree of unanimity by the central
committee and completely suited to the party's valuable tradition
of renovation, continuation and development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Le Kha Phieu said Vietnam's achievements have proven the
correctness of the economic policy adopted by the party.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed that Vietnam is still facing many
difficulties on the road of development, and that the fourth
plenum of the Communist Party gave priority to the need to enhance
self-sovereignty and self-reliance.
</P>
<P>
However, Le Kha Phieu said, the Vietnamese government
"advocated global and regional integration at an early date,"
fully aware of the opportunities and challenges ahead.
</P>
<P>
The fourth plenum of the party reiterated the country's resolve
to participate in the global and regional integration, while
stressing the necessity to preserve the national character and
protect the national interests, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Only enhanced self-sovereignty and self-reliance can ensure
efficiency in integration and secure good conditions for the
national construction and development," said the party chief.
</P>
</TEXT>
