<HEADLINE> Russian Composer Georgy Sviridov Dies at 82 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moscow, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Georgy Sviridov, one of Russia's
most prominent composers this century, died of a heart attack
Tuesday morning at Moscow's Central Clinical Hospital. He was 82.
</P>
<P>
Sviridov had made an invaluable contribution to the cultural
treasury of Russia and the world, Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin was quoted as saying by Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin expressed deep regret at Sviridov's death.
</P>
<P>
Sviridov was decorated with, among some other top Soviet
awards, the Lenin Prize. 
</P>
</TEXT>
