<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Enjoys Drama Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
this evening enjoyed the performance of the drama "the Tiger Takes
Over Mt Zhongshan."
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also the general secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist party of China and chairman of the
Central Military Commission, met with a group of local artists and
playwrights prior to the performance.
</P>
<P>
The performance was a major part of the ongoing memorial
activities to mark the 90th anniversary of drama performances in
the country.
</P>
<P>
The drama, presented by the Frontier Drama Troupe under the
Nanjing Military Area Command of the People's Liberation Army, tells
the first military university of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The school, which was founded by Marshal Liu Bocheng,
witnesses the many changes of the People's Liberation Army since
the 1950s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
