<HEADLINE> Nepali Finance Minister Defends VAT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Finance Minister
Rabindra Nath Sharma said Tuesday that the government introduced
the value added tax (VAT) because it will do away with aberrations
and anomalies in the existing tax system.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating a discussion program on the VAT held in Morang
District of eastern Nepal, the finance minister said that as a
scientific accounting system characterized by transparency, the
VAT will be of concrete help in running business and industry
through healthy competition.
</P>
<P>
There should be cooperation between businesses, industry and
the bureaucracy to make the VAT a success, the official RSS news
agency quoted Sharma as saying.
</P>
<P>
He assured his audience that octroi would be abolished.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government formally introduced the VAT on November
16, 1997 despite strong opposition from the business community.
</P>
<P>
Sharma has defended the VAT on several occasions since then.
</P>
</TEXT>
