<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Opens Largest Phosphorus Fertilizer Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Dayukou
Project, a leading state project built with World Bank loans,
came to a successful conclusion today.
</P>
<P>
The completion of the project signifies the beginning of the
Hubei Jingxiang Phosphorus Chemical Industry Group Company, the
largest phosphorus fertilizer production base in the country. The
company is located in the city of Zhongxiang, central China's
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The project was completed at a cost of 3.67 billion yuan (440
million US dollars), including a World Bank loan of one billion
yuan (120 million US dollars). Primary mining and ore dressing
equipment for the new complex was imported from the United States,
Japan, Germany and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
According to Zeng Chungou, chairman of the board of its
directors, his company has set up eight subsidiary companied,
basically forming a complete process ranging from mining, ore
dressing, to the production of acids and chemical fertilizers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
