<HEADLINE> Holiday Death Toll on S. African Roads Rises to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The death toll on South
African roads since December 1 has risen to 812 by this
afternoon, South African Press Association quoted the "Arrive
Alive" road safety awareness campaign as saying.
</P>
<P>
The fatality breakdown is 356 passengers, 264 pedestrians and
192 drivers.
</P>
<P>
The majority of accidents were attributed to speeding, driver
fatigue as well as jaywalking.
</P>
<P>
Most deaths were reported in Kwazulu-Natal Province with 142,
followed closely by Eastern Cape (137) and Gauteng (134).
</P>
<P>
Last year, 1,242 people were killed in traffic accidents
during the Christmas and New Year holiday season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
