<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chissano to Attend African Summit with World Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- President Joaquim Chissano will
attend the African summit with the World Bank to be held on
January 24 in the Ugandan capital of Kampala, a Mozambican
government official confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
According to Eneas Comiche, Minister in the Presidency for
Social and Economic Affairs, the summit is aimed at discussing
the role of World Bank in Africa.
</P>
<P>
During the summit, which will be an "informal" one with the
bank's leading institutions, the African heads of state or
governments will consult with the international monetary agency
on new spheres for cooperation on the basis of the reality of the
continent.
</P>
<P>
Comiche noted that the meeting will be deemed as a way to
"convey the views of Africans" to the World Bank and "impose
pressure" on its development program.
</P>
<P>
In order to attend the meeting, Chissano will have to cut
short his 30-day vacation starting December 31.
</P>
<P>
The summit, sponsored by Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni,
will draw presidents from Tanzania, Rwanda, Ethiopia, Eritrea,
the Democratic Republic of Congo, Botswana, Zimbabwe, Zambia and
Senegal, as well as Jamos Wolfensohm, governor of the World Bank
</P>
</TEXT>
