<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Insurance companies in Britain
face an estimated claims bill of 500 million pounds (815 million
U.S. dollars) for damage inflicted in one of the worst storms of
the decade, local press reports said Tuesday.
</P>
