<HEADLINE> UK Employers Fail to Find Employable Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- British big companies are finding
it difficult to get the graduates they need, local press reports
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Citing figures from the Association of Graduate Recruiters
(AGR), reports said that the country's biggest employers such as
BT (British Telecom), IBM, Shell, interviewed an average of 100
graduates for every job, but more than half of them failed to fill
all their vacancies in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The AGR said that nearly half of those companies had a
shortfall of more than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that since 1993, more and more employers felt
frustrated and the number of frustrated firms had now reached the
highest level since 1989.
</P>
<P>
The association pointed out,"it must be a matter of concern
that at a time of continued increase in the graduate supply, over
half of the major recruiters in this country experience
difficulties in securing the number and quality of graduates they
need." 
</P>
