Georgian-Abkhazian settlement, "has held and is holding the view
that the way to stop the conflict is that through peaceful
political negotiations between the sides."
</P>
<P>
Russian troops, as part of the collective peacekeeping force
from the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), carry out a
peacekeeping operation in the zone of the Georgian-Abkhazian
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the Russian troops, the spokesman also said, peace
has been preserved there for more than three years, and over
50,000 refugees have returned to the Galy district. This has
proved the high effectiveness of peacekeeping efforts in Abkhazia,
he added. 
