<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Finland has become the
first member state of the United Nations to pay in full its
assessed contribution to the UN regular budget for 1998, a release
from the spokesman office said today.
</P>
<P>
The release said Finland paid 5.6 million U.S. dollars to the
United Nations Monday.
</P>
