<HEADLINE> First French Group Realizes 35 Hour Work Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The French group Cofinoga which is
specialized in providing credit to consumers, today became the
first enterprise to realize the 35 hour work week plan, reported
Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
The management of Cofinoga and several trade unions signed an
agreement on 35 hour work week on September 30 last year, which
will allow the group to create 182 jobs, said the group's
management.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, all employees and managers of the group will be paid
the same salary as they worked 39 hours.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, approved by the Ministry of Employment and
Solidarity, also planned to create an addition of saved hours for
all employees and make more flexible working schedules to allow
them to vary from 20 to 42 hours a week.
</P>
<P>
The reduction of working time will be mainly realized through
cutting daily working hours, four-day work week, and additional
rest days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
