today by three members of the family of his victim's in a classic
settling of account, according to Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Jacques Adler killed Michel Weiss on December 25, 1992, in a
dispute between two Gypsy families in Haguenau in Bas Rhin,
eastern France.
