<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Series on Zhou Enlai Debuted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- A 12-part television documentary
series marking the 100 birth anniversary of late Chinese Premier
Zhou Enlai debuted in the Great Hall of the People here this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Revolutionary Bo Yibo penned the inscription for the
title of the series jointly produced by the Beijing Television
Station (BTV), the China International Cultural Exchange Center,
the Qingdao Shuangxing (Double Star) Group and the Golden Rose
Cultural Communication Company.
</P>
<P>
The series was directed by famous Chinese film director Deng
Zaijun.
</P>
<P>
The production team spent two full years traveling to numerous
places and interviewing several hundred people in order to present
more vivid stories depicting the life of the late
premier. Moreover, a host of dignitaries overseas voluntarily
contacted the production team and told its members about Zhou's
moral integrity as well as their admiration and high esteem for
the late leader. Analysts have called the series a production of
"epic proportions".
</P>
<P>
More than 100 noted figures from various walks of life in the
Chinese capital attended this evening's debut, including General
Zhang Zhen, Lei Jieqiong, Wu Jieping, Li Desheng, Xiao Ke and Peng
Chong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
