<HEADLINE> Holiday Traffic Leaves 380 Casualties in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents, 160 of them in
Spain during the Christmas season from December 19 to January 6,
left 186 people dead and 194 others injured.
</P>
<P>
Of those wounded, 122 suffered serious injuries.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, said traffic authorities in Spain, the previous
Christmas season saw 164 traffic accidents resulting in 497
casualties -- 205 dead and 292 injured.
</P>
<P>
Some of the accidents, analysts said, was because people drank
too much or were high on drugs before joining the holiday traffic,
despite there were 8,000 police officers trying to stop them.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the last day of the season, 30 people lost their
lives or became disabled on road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
