<HEADLINE> Rockets Win Through, Hunters Revenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions August First
Rockets proved a class above the mid-table Jinan Army Pegasus,
beating their army opponents 107-74 on Wednesday's 13th round
Chinese basketball first division league.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets, which are well on the way to reign the title with
just one lose mid-way into the league, keep their leading on the
overall standings with 25 points.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets made advantage of the Pegasus' 14 turnovers to
scored .519 from the field and dunked nine three-points in their
22 attempts.
</P>
<P>
Chen Zhaosheng took 12 boards, accounting for half of the total
of the Pegasus, and Lou Yangdong sunk four beyong the line, also
half of the number of his team, but the Pegasus, six wins and
seven loses, were no match with the powerhouse Rockest either on
experience or on strength.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets are still one win more than the unremmitting
chasers Shandong Flaming Bulls which trounced home 80-58 the
struggling Lianhang Army Eagles, which are two wins and 11 loses
with 15 points.
</P>
<P>
The team top scorer Gong Xiaobin chipped in game-high 33
points and 11 boards, also the most in the game for the Bulls,
which made 31 from 58 in the field.
</P>
<P>
The Liaoning Hunters made the revenge of their loses in the
road to the Beijing Ducks, winning 86-66 at home.
</P>
<P>
The Hunters, last year's runners-up, dented the Ducks pointless
and committing seven fouls in the opening five minutes in the
second half, pulling away from a 46-36 before the break.
</P>
<P>
The Hunters, who were stunned by their rivals 81-80 in the
first round match, rested their key players in the final minutes
and sent their backups on the court against the Ducks center Shan
Tao, who scored 32 points.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere, the Zhejiang Squarrels losed to Sichuan Pandas at
home 91-78, Jiangsu Dragons downed Shanghai Sharks 80-58 and
Guangdong Tigers piled up a 86-65 win over Shenyang Army Lions.
</P>
</TEXT>
