<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Government Attaches Importance to HK Autonomy: Anson Chan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese central government
attaches great importance to the high degree of autonomy of the
Hong Kong government and the implementation of the policy of "one
country, two systems" in Hong Kong, a senior Hong Kong official
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Anson Chan, administrative secretary of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China, told reporters upon her
return to Hong Kong from a three-day work visit to Beijing that
her trip had been very useful.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Beijing, Chan discussed matters related to
the Hong Kong SAR with Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, Director Liao
Hui of the Office of Hong Kong and Macao Affairs under the State
Council and other senior officials of various departments of the
central government.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed his strong confidence in the Hong Kong SAR, Chan
said. She quoted Qian as saying in particular that the civil
servants of the SAR have played an important role in maintaining
Hong Kong's stability.
</P>
<P>
Chan said that Qian also asked her to visit Beijing and other
provinces in the mainland more often to increase understanding and
 communication with officials of various sectors.
</P>
<P>
Chan said that during her talks with Liao, Liao stressed that
he will strictly abide by the Basic Law and implement the policies
of "one country, two systems" and a high degree of autonomy in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Liao made it clear that if needed, his office will provide
support for the SAR government's work, but will never interfere
with its operation, Chan said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
