<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Match has overtaken
Dennis Conner's Toshiba to grab a narrow lead in the fourth leg of
the Whitbread Round the World Race.
</P>
<P>
Skippered by Gunnar Krantz and Erle Williams, Swedish Match
caught up from 0.7 nautical miles behind Toshiba to take a 5.7
miles lead as the fleet arrives at Cape Reinga, the northernmost
tip of New Zealand.
</P>
