<HEADLINE> Road Accident Casualties Fall in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The deaths from road accidents in
Vietnam dropped in 1997, but the government is still concerned
about the high number of deaths of the kind.
</P>
<P>
According to government figures, 5,680 people died last year on
the roads with some 75 percent of the accidents caused by bad
driving.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 21,905 people were injured in road
accidents in 1997, which government officials and police have
described as "serious and worrying."
</P>
<P>
The official figures showed that the number of cars rose by
12.3 percent in 1997 while the number of motorbikes increased by
20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The traffic police said that there are around five million
motorbikes and 418,000 cars in Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
