<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Builds Digital Mobile Telephone Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui province has
built a digital mobile telephone network.
</P>
<P>
The digital mobile telephone network has nine digital mobile
telephone switching centers with a total of 440,000 lines, and 727
base radio stations.
</P>
<P>
The network serves all the cities and more than 80 percent of
the towns in the province.
</P>
<P>
In addition, mobile telephone subscribers in Anhui can contact
their relatives and friends in nearly 300 cities and 1,400
counties in China, and in more than 30 countries and regions.
