<HEADLINE> Singapore, Thailand Open Civil Service Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Thai Foreign Minister
Surin Pitsuwan opened the first Singapore-Thailand Civil Service
Exchange Program here on Wednesday to strengthen bilateral
cooperation in human resources development.
</P>
<P>
Surin, who arrived here Tuesday on a two-day visit at the
invitation of Singapore Foreign Minister S. Jayakumar, stressed
the need for such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The program will bring together senior civil servants to
discuss a range of bilateral issues. Besides, Thai students will
be offered 30 Singapore scholarships to study at top secondary
schools and junior colleges here.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, qualified university students will receive guaranteed
financial aid packages for study at the National University of
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Singapore Productivity and Standards Board
will help Thailand launch its own Skills Development Fund and
Quality Award Scheme, which is part of several initiatives
proposed under the exchange program.
</P>
<P>
Singapore and Thailand also agreed to hold joint courses for
developing countries in civil aviation, public service management
and water supply technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
