<HEADLINE> Shanxi Selects Big, Medium-Size Enterprise Directors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The old, conventional practice
of the government appointing directors of state-owned factories in
north China's Shanxi Province is giving way to the new method of
public nominations and selections through a democratic process.
</P>
<P>
The fact that public opinion is sought during the process has
enabled common workers to play a bigger role in the selection of
their bosses.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the new method was used to select the presidents
and/or directors for 192 state-owned firms, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
The new practice enables the qualified individuals to seek
leading posts in state-owned enterprises on their own, or through
recommendations by Party organizations or their colleagues.
</P>
</TEXT>
