<HEADLINE> Singapore Stresses Commitment to Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Deputy Prime
Minister and Defense Minister Tony Tan said on Wednesday that
despite the current economic downturn, Singapore must be prepared
to commit resources to ensure the country's security.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an event marking the completion of the upgrading of
the Singapore Air Force's F-5 Tiger, Tan said that building a
credible defense force is a long-term process which requires
prudent and steady investment over many years.
</P>
<P>
He said that the peace of mind the Singaporeans and investors
have is due to Singapore's defense philosophy, which is to be
prepared at all times for any eventuality.
</P>
<P>
