congratulatory letter marking the opening of the conference.
</P>
<P>
The ordnance industry, a basic sector facing great
difficulties, plays an important role in advancing the
modernization of national defense, according to Wu, who is also a
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the industry focused on reversing decreasing economic
returns by restructuring operations, introducing new management
strategies and expanding its product mix.
</P>
<P>
A majority of enterprises in the sector are expected to recoup
deficits over the next three years, according to Wu.
</P>
<P>
The industry has substantially increased its output of products
for civilian use, including automobiles and motorcycles. In
addition, its 1997 output of mini-buses exceeded 127,000
units. The sector is also encouraging the establishment of an
increasing number of enterprise groups. 
