<HEADLINE> Epidemic Prevention Efforts in Snowstorm Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Local medical departments in Nagqu
Prefecture, an area in the northern part of the Tibet Autonomous
Regions struck by heavy snowstorms, have worked out active,
effective measures to prevent the outbreak of epidemics.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of medical teams, dispatched by local governments and
units of the People's Liberation Army (PLA), have been working in
the area, according to Adain, executive vice-president of the
Autonomous Regional Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
Heavy snowstorms devastating Nagqu Prefecture since last
September have created enormous difficulties for local life and
production.
</P>
<P>
As part of an effort to prevent the possible outbreak of
epidemic diseases in the area, local medical authorities have sent
teams of experts to look into the situation and have followed-up
by dispatching medical teams to carry out prevention programs.
</P>
<P>
Adain said local medical teams are capable of preventing the
outbreak of any form of epidemic disease. The Regional Health Care
Bureau have provided epidemic prevention drugs valued at 240,000
yuan.
</P>
<P>
No epidemic outbreaks have been reported in Nagqu so far, said
Adain.
</P>
<P>
A general mood of order and serenity is prevalent in the
region, where local government departments and schools are in
operation as usual, so as post offices and telecommunication
networks. Shops along main roads are packed with all commodities
and, in grocers and free markets there are abundant meat foods as
well as a dozen varieties of fresh vegetables from Lhasa and the
neighbouring Qinghai province.
</P>
<P>
Yet, urgent meetings are in session in prefectural government
offices, and a number of work teams have gone among snowstorm
victims to lead them in rescue work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
