The joint-stock bank, established in 1988, had 30 billion
yuan in total assets, 3.5 billion yuan in net assets, and 2.7
billion yuan in profits at the end of November, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The bank's network has expanded to include 10 provincial
branches, 20 sub-branches and 31 representative offices, in
addition to its affiliated Fujian Industrial Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Over the past nine years, the Fujian Industrial Bank has
attached great importance to improving its operation to meet the
needs for the development of the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The bank has granted 75 billion yuan in loans to support pillar
industries, major enterprises and key projects in Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, the bank has raised 159 million US
dollars in commercial or syndicated loans from the international
market to promote the development of Fujian's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the bank's stable operation is partly
reflected by its emphasis on establishing and improving internal
control mechanisms and preventing and limiting financial risks.
 
