<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Speedy Economic Growth In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province had a
GDP of 270 billion yuan in 1997, up 13 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
Local annual economic growth was nearly 17 percent during the
1992-1997 period, 5.6 percentage points higher than the national
average. This growth has helped make Anhui one of the provinces
with speediest economic growth in central China.
</P>
<P>
The development comes as a result of local efforts to improve
transportation, postal service, telecommunications, power
industry, and in the increased use of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The province's agriculture grew 9 percent last year, industry
grew 16 percent, and the service trade, 14 percent.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's price controls have been effective and last year it had
a record with no price increases from 1996 levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
