<HEADLINE> Eastern China Province Becoming Major Flower Grower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
blossomed into a flower center, with 6,666 ha of land now devoted
to producing flowers and flowering plants.
</P>
<P>
The province is famous nationwide for its roses, Chinese roses,
peonies, azaleas, and chrysanthemums, which sell well both in
other parts of China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Shandong now has more than 1,100 businesses that grow flowers,
and which employ more than 500,000 people.
</P>
<P>
It also has more than 20 wholesale flower markets, which do
more than a billion yuan in business annually, so the flower
industry is expected to contribute a great deal to local economic
growth in future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
