<HEADLINE> China's Team Scales African Highest Peak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's team scaled the
5,895-meter Mount Jilimanjaro, the African highest peak, at 7:40
(local time) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The team, headed by Li Zhixin, started its first attemp at 2:00
(local time) despite the fiercest storm for three years.
</P>
<P>
This is the sixth highset peak Li has conquered in his plan to
sweep all the highest peaks in seven continents.
</P>
<P>
The team is heading for the 5,030-meter-height Mt. Puncak Jaya
in the Oceania in November.
</P>
<P>
Li, teamed up with Wang Yongfeng, has scaled the Asian highest
Mt. Qomolangma (8,848 meters), the North American highest
Mt. Mickinley (6,194 meters), the South American highest
Mt. Aconcagua (6,964 meters), the European highest Mt. Gora
El'brus (5,642 meters) and the Antarctican highest Mt. Vinsen
(5,114 meters). 
</P>
</TEXT>
