<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Italian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress,
met here today with a parliamentary delegation from the
Center-Left Coalition of Italy.
</P>
<P>
Wang noted that since 1970, when China and Italy established
diplomatic ties, friendship and cooperation between the two
countries have developed steadily and the two parliaments have
also established close relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang also expressed his confidence that the delegation's visit
will promote the development of friendship and cooperation between
the two countries and the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
He expressed great appreciation for Italy's position on "one
China", and its refusal to support a bill against China tabled at
last year's meeting of the United Nations Human Rights Commission.
</P>
<P>
Fabio Mussi, head of the delegation from the Chamber of
Deputies representing the Center-Left Democratic Party, said the
Italian government and parliament have adopted a positive attitude
toward the development of relations with China.
</P>
<P>
The Italian delegation is visiting China at the invitation of
the International Department of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China.  
