<HEADLINE> APPF Annual Conference Opens in Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The 6th annual conference of the
Asia-Pacific Parliamentary Forum (APPF) opened here on Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Some 195 delegates from 24 countries are attending the four-day
APPF conference to discuss and pass 33 draft resolutions in
politics, economy, security, trade and investment liberalization
in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The current financial crisis Southeast Asian countries and
South Korea and how to stabilize the region's troubled financial
markets are expected to dominate the conference.
</P>
<P>
