<HEADLINE> Southwestern City Prepares For World Horticulture Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Preparations are under way for
the world horticulture fair, which is scheduled to be held in
China's southwestern city of Kunming in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Five exhibition halls, three outdoor exhibition areas and the
framework of public facilities are being built on the site of the
exhibition covering 218 hectares. Other related facilities such as
expansion work at Kunming International Airport are also well
under way.
</P>
<P>
Since Chinese Premier Li Peng sent invitations to 162
countries, nearly 50 nations have applied to participate in
the '99 Kunming Horticulture Fair. Japan, France, Egypt and
Switzerland have decided to build outdoor galleries reflecting
their own cultures.
</P>
<P>
To guarantee the fair's sound operation, organizers have
pledged their support and assistance to participants.
</P>
<P>
The organizers will provide free land to participants for their
outdoor galleries, a 10,000-square-meter multi-purpose hall and
free mud.
</P>
<P>
Organizers also will provide participants with relevant
documents that detail services and technical specifications of the
facilities for modifications by participants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
