<HEADLINE> 40 Killed in Central Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIGALI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Forty people were murdered in
two Rwandan communes of Central Gitarama Prefecture early this
week, officials in the area told the Rwanda News Agency today.
</P>
<P>
According to Col. Balthazar Ndengeyinka, Commander of
Gitarama-Kibuye Brigade, a large group of "Interahamwe" militia
armed with guns, machetes, and axes massacred 14 peasants Monday
night in Nyabikenke commune, north of Gitarama town.
</P>
<P>
"The attack occurred at 7:00 p.m and was perpetrated by
assailants from neighbouring Ndusu commune in northern Ruhengeri
prefecture," he said.
</P>
<P>
Two people were critically wounded and are currently being
treated at Kabgayi Hospital in Gitarama. The victims included two
genocide orphans as well as two grass-root administrative
leaders.
</P>
<P>
The same Monday night, another group of "Interahamwe"
militiamen attacked Nyakabanda commune, killing 26 people using
guns, grenades, and all sorts of traditional weapons.
</P>
<P>
Before withdrawing to neighbouring Satinskyi commune, south of
Gisenyi prefecture, the killers left leaflets threatening local
residents that "whoever tries to oppose them will have his head
cut off." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
