<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Biggest Toys Fair Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong, the world's leading
toy exporter, opened Asia's largest toys show here Wednesday
with the participation of a record number of exhibitors.
</P>
<P>
At the 24th Hong Kong Toys and Games Fair, more than 1,400 toys
manufacturers and dealers from 27 countries and regions have set
up their display stalls, occupying a total of 46,000 square meters
in five halls at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Both the number of exhibitors and the exhibition space have
increased by nearly 50 percent compared with the previous fair in
1996, according to the organizer, the Hong Kong Trade Development
Council (TDC).
</P>
<P>
The exhibition zone is divided into eight sections, featuring a
 variety of products -- soft toys and dolls, mechanical toys and
action figures, educational toys and games, battery-operated and
electronic toys, baby toys, gifts, outdoor and sporting items,
and parts and accessories.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 local toy makers are taking part in the four-day
fair.
</P>
<P>
"We're still the world's leading exporters of toys and the
industry is growing bigger and better," said Edmund Young,
chairman of the TDC Toys Advisory Committee, at the opening
ceremony Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the success of Hong Kong toy companies to their
consistent focus on high quality and innovative designs.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of 1997, Hong Kong's total exports of
toys reached 77.76 billion HK dollars (about 10 billion U.S.
dollars), up 10 percent from the same period of 1996, according to
Young.
</P>
<P>
Between January and October in 1997, exports to the United
States, which took in nearly half of Hong Kong's exports of toys,
also rose by 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although it is difficult to predict the performance in 1998,
Young said: "We can expect continued demand from many key markets
like the United States and Western Europe."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
