<HEADLINE> Indian People Tired of Instability: Vajpayee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 7 (Xinhua)-- A.B. Vajpayee, senior leader of
India's Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) and its candidate for prime
minister, said Wednesday that people are tired of instability and
are looking forward to a stable government.
</P>
<P>
"They see the BJP, the biggest opposition party in India, as
the only option before them," he said at a press conference in
Jalna, Maharashtra State during his campaign tour.
</P>
<P>
The electorate would give a clear-cut verdict in the coming
general elections and there is no possibility of a hung
parliament, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The combination of BJP and its allies will definitely succeed
as it would emerge as the single largest party with others
supporting it," he said.
</P>
<P>
On economic issues, Vajpayee said the government has a role to
play in providing basic infrastructural facilities like power and
roads.  
