<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Reaches 3.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Macao's inflation for the first 11
months of 1997 reached 3.6 percent, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Wednesday also show that inflation rate for the 12-month period
dating back from last November reached 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The composite consumer price index (CCPI) in November grew 2.4
percent from the same month in 1996. But it dropped 0.2 percent
from last October.
</P>
<P>
The price decline in November was due mainly to lower cost of
transportation and foodstuff excluding alcoholic drinks. But the
price index of garments and footwear rose a bit in November.
</P>
<P>
Macao's economic growth has been slowing down since 1993, and
the growth rate of 1997 is estimated at less than one percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
