<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Anti-narcotics unit in Kampala
detained 356 suspects over drug dealing and possession last year,
''the New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,900 kilograms of cannabis have been recovered and
980 plants destroyed in the period.
</P>
<P>
At the Entebbe airport alone, the authorities have arrested 32
people, most of them foreigners, for the possession of drugs, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda was used by drug smugglers as an intermediary station
from Latin America and Asia to Europe and the U.S. in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that anti-narcotic unit in the country
arrested only one tenth of the drug smugglers due to lack of
equipment to detect drugs.
</P>
<P>
To improve the situation, Uganda is now buying new equipment
and sending its anti-narcotic personnel abroad for training, the
report said. 
