<HEADLINE> British Universities to Launch Exhibition in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 British
universities for the first time will show their academic pride
with an exhibition before a nation with a 5,000-year-old
educational tradition this weekend in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the biggest one on international education in
China in recent years, is expected to help both sides better
understand each other and expand cooperation, the State Education
Commission said today.
</P>
<P>
Great Britain has been considered a worldwide pioneer of modern
education, and it has the reputation of cultivating outstanding
and excellent students. With a somewhat rigid but plain
educational style, the country is in the process of adopting
reforms to transform the sector while adhering to tradition.
</P>
<P>
China has been carrying out educational reforms to topple the
Soviet model for the past decade. The country's latest policies
encourage the introduction of advanced educational experiences
from other countries.
</P>
<P>
Britain is a major destination for Chinese who study
abroad. There are 8,000 Chinese studying in the British Isles, and
the number is increasing.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is being sponsored by the China Education
Association for International Exchanges and the British Embassy in
Beijing. Representatives will include Oxford and Cambridge among
other British universities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
