<HEADLINE> China's Nuclear Industry Becoming Powerhouse (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's nuclear industry is
becoming a new powerhouse of the national economy after the sector
completed a strategic shift from military production to civilian
application.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua today, Zhang Huazhu, deputy general
manager of the China Nuclear Industry Corp., explained that the
adjustment, which has taken two decades to complete, was designed
to improve the industrial structure and development plans for the
country's nuclear industry.
</P>
<P>
"China's nuclear industry is now operating under a new system
featuring a combination of military and civilian production,
development of nuclear power and a diversified economy, with
nuclear as the foundation," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, the nuclear sector has established a large
number of enterprise groups over the past few years in the
economically-developed coastal areas such as Shanghai, east China,
and Guangdong Province of south China and has developed more than
1,500 kinds of civilian products.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear industrial economy has been expanding in China by
maintaining a high growth rate in a succession of years, resulting
in remarkable improvement in the country's comprehensive economic
strength.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output of civilian products now makes up over 80
percent of China's nuclear industrial output, which is 20 times
the total when adjusting efforts first began.
</P>
<P>
Development of nuclear power is a major way for the industry to
make strategic adjustments, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
