<HEADLINE> China's First National Anti-Drug Exhibition to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's first national anti-drug
exhibition is scheduled to be held in the capital next May or June.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the exhibition is to "Love Your Life and Reject the
Drug."
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Anti-Narcotics Committee said that
the exhibition aims to give a strong push to the nationwide
anti-narcotics campaign and presents a special gift to the
upcoming Special Session on Drug Control of the United Nations
General Assembly to be held in June.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is expected to tell audiences about the harmful
consequences of taking narcotics; the history and reality of
drug-related problems in China; the principles, policies, laws and
regulations concerning narcotics; and the achievements made by the
Chinese government in the war against drugs.
</P>
<P>
The official said the exhibition will offer precautionary
education to the audiences in a bid to strengthen youngsters'
capability to resist narcotics and enhance the people's awareness
to join the nationwide anti-drug campaign.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will support its theme through photos, video and
audio products. 
