<HEADLINE> Rose Wins 10km Open Water Swimming in Perth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Erica Rose of the United States
won the women's 5-kilometer open water swimming with an impressive
clocking of 59 minutes and 23.50 seconds at the world swimming
championships here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rose pulled ahead in the later part of the race to beat Edith
van Dijk of the Netherlands into second place. Van Dijk timed
1:00.58.80.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Peggy Buchse came third in 1:01.05.80.
</P>
<P>
"In the beginning it was really tough, in the second half I
just decided to take off," Rose said after the race.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the morning, Russian Alexei Akatiev triumphed in the
men's 5-kilometer race in a time of 55:18.60, with pre-race
favorite Ky Hurst of Australia second in 55.24.90. 
</P>
