<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Blood Cells Found Intact on 400-year-old Human Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Experts in Nanjing, capital of
east China's Jiangsu Province, recently discovered complete red
blood cells in the lung of a 400-year-old male body. The cells'
shape reportedly was intact, and they had a clear structure and
bright color similar to that in living creatures.
</P>
<P>
According to today's Shanghai-based Wen Hui Daily, the body,
unearthed last July in Dantu County, was identified as the remains
of a county magistrate during the Ming dynasty (1368-1644). His
surname was Jiang and he died at the age of 45.
</P>
<P>
"It is unimaginable that 400-year-old red cells are still in
good conditions," said Xu Yongqing, a researcher from the Shanghai
Museum of Natural History, adding that the discovery is the first
of its kind in China's ancient corpse research.
</P>
<P>
Experts explained that in previous cases only remains of cells
could be found. They considered the new discovery a key to the
mystery of how Chinese ancestors protected bodies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980107.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Ringgit Undervalued: Finance Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister and Finance Minister Anwar Ibrahim said Wednesday that
the local currency, the ringgit, has now become grossly
undervalued in an environment of highly unstable market
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit dropped sharply to the 4.7 level against the U.S.
dollar at midday from 4.22 earlier in the morning.
</P>
<P>
"While Malaysia will continue to pursue a policy of flexible
exchange rates, these rates should reflect the underlying
fundamentals. It should not be a situation in which the exchange
rate determines the fundamentals," Anwar said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
He noted that for an open economy such as Malaysia, these
developments, if allowed to persist over a prolonged period, will
be damaging to the economic and financial fundamentals.
</P>
<P>
"Intervention operations" have been conducted to ensure stable
conditions to allow for the efficient functioning of the foreign
exchange market, he said.
</P>
<P>
Policies have now been put in place to ensure the medium and
long-term prospects of the economy, Anwar said, adding, "We are
confident that these policies will increase the resilience of the
economy and financial system in adjusting during this difficult
period."  
</P>
</TEXT>
