</P>
<P>
-- Nigerian Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi Tuesday declared at a
meeting with the African group of ambassadors that the federal
government had enough evidence to suspect possible foreign
involvement in last December's aborted move the overthrow the
present administration.
</P>
<P>
New Nigerian
</P>
<P>
