<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT January 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Opposition leader Raila Odinga has accepted the
results of the December 29 General Election and congratulated
President Daniel arap Moi on his victory, according to a Daily
Nation report Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Odinga dropped his earlier rejection of election results and
demand for repeat elections within 21 days which he made jointly
with Democratic Party Chairman Mwai Kibaki last
Friday. (Kenya-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Normal life and business in Bangladesh have nearly
come to a standstill due to days of cold wave and fog all over
the country.
</P>
<P>
The country's national airline, Biman, had canceled all its
domestic flights and delayed all its international flights due to
the poor visibility caused by the thick sheet of fog, press
reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On the Dhaka-Aricha highway, a seven-kilometer-long queue of
vehicles was formed as dense fog disrupted ferry service in two
routes from the Aricha and Nawa ghats. (Bangladesh-Cold Wave)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy's employment rate will rise to 59.1 percent in
1998 and 59.3 percent in 1999 from 59 percent in 1997, said a
survey issued by the Organization for Economic Cooperation and
Development (OECD) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the improved rate will still be the lowest in the
Group of Seven (G-7) industrialized countries, said the 29-member
OECD which expects its average employment rate to climb to 70.7
percent in 1999 from 70.4 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Italy's employment rate would also be lower than the European
Union's average of 67.1 percent in 1999, it
added. (Italy-Employment Rate)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- The renminbi yuan is unlikely to be devalued even
though the sharp depreciation of currencies in neighbouring
countries will inevitably affect China's export trade, according
to an authoritative source.
</P>
<P>
A financial official who declined to be identified said the
world market should maintain its confidence in the renminbi rate's
stability. The marginal changes in the rate that follow the market
demand and supply are normal, he was quoted as saying in
Wednesday's China Daily. (China-Renminbi-Stable)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- The Little Mermaid statue, located on the
waterfront of Danish capital of Copenhagen, was decapitated
overnight in a new attack, the second one since 1964.
</P>
<P>
Police said Tuesday that the head of the small bronze figure
was sawn off by unknown culprits and there were no clues.
</P>
<P>
Divers scoured the harbor bottom for the head on Tuesday, but
had not found it.
</P>
<P>
The world-famous Little Mermaid statue first lost her head in
1964 and her arm was sawn off in 1985. They were replaced as the
mould was well preserved. (Denmark-Mermaid) 
</P>
</TEXT>
