<HEADLINE> Uganda to Reshuffle Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni will soon announce a major cabinet reshuffle affecting
six positions, ''the New Vision'' disclosed today.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a top source in the government, the newspaper said the
reorganization aimed at improving efficiency will come within a
few days.
</P>
<P>
President Museveni has just reshuffled the defense system,
naming Salim Saleh, the former special presidential adviser on
political and military affairs in the north as the acting state
minister for defense.
</P>
<P>
Former state minister for defense Major-General Amama Mbabazi
was re-appointed as the state minister in charge of political
affairs in the presidential office, to replace Medi Kaggwa.
</P>
<P>
Another state minister for defense Jeje Odongo was shifted to
the post of army commander.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier James Kazini was named as the acting chief of staff
to replace Brigadier Chefe Ali. 
</P>
</TEXT>
