<HEADLINE> Uganda Police Equipped With New Communication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Uganda police have received
sophisticated communication equipment, enabling them to link with
the rest of the world within seconds, ''the New Vision'' paper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A source in Police Criminal Investigation Department said the
x400 communication network was given to Uganda recently by the
Secretariat of International Crime Police Organization
(Interpol).
</P>
<P>
The equipment was commissioned by John Cossy Odomel, the
Inspector General of Police of the country.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Interpol Squad has smooth relations with Interpol, and
it has connected to the eastern African regional Interpol bureau
in Nairobi. 
