<HEADLINE> New Electronics Industrial Zone in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The electronics industry has a
new base in the New Pudong Area's Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The main products are computer chips, disc drives, and color
printers.
</P>
<P>
For the last three years, investors from the United States,
Japan, Britain, France, Italy, the Netherlands, Singapore, Hong
Kong, and Taiwan have put 500 million US dollars into the area.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the growth of foreign-funded
electronics firms here is because of preferential policies like
tax exemptions or tax refunding.
</P>
<P>
The foreign investors include such international giants as
Intel, IBM, AT&AMP;T and Philips. 
</P>
</TEXT>
