<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host ASEAN Tourism Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The southern Philippine city of
Cebu will host the ASEAN Tourism Forum (ATF) '98 from January 9 to
15 to promote tourism cooperation in the Southeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
The annual event involves all the tourism industry sectors of
the nine members of ASEAN (the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations): Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers of tourism and the heads of tourism
organizations from member countries will hold a formal meeting
during the period, the Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the forum, which has the theme of "ASEAN Tourism:
Traveling Time", each country will also showcase their best
travel, assets and tourism potentials, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The most important component of the ATF is the Travel Exchange,
a tourism marketing activity geared to opening opportunities for
suppliers of ASEAN travel products and services.
</P>
<P>
It will be a gathering of more than 1,000 buyers and sellers.
At least some 500 international wholesale and retail travel agents
and event planners will join the Travel Exchange as buyers.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Corpuz, Executive Director of the Philippine Convention
and Visitors Corporation, said "Cebu City is ready, willing and
able to welcome the more than 1,500 delegates to its shores."
</P>
<P>
The ATF is a cooperative regional organization to promote the
ASEAN region as one tourism destination. It is composed of the
ASEAN Tourism Association, the Federation of ASEAN Travel
Associations and the ASEAN Hotel Association.
</P>
<P>
Each group will hold a half-day meeting during the forum to
outline their respective plans and programs in further improving
the quality and standards of the tourism industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
