<HEADLINE> China, Sri Lanka Sign MOU on Industrial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China and Sri Lanka signed a
memorandum of understanding (MOU) on bilateral cooperation in
petroleum and petrochemical industries here Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, penned by Gu Xiulian, minister of chemical
industry of China, and Anuruddha Ratwatte, minister of irrigation
and power of Sri Lanka, the two sides will conduct scientific,
technical and commercial cooperation in fields of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises will be encouraged to carry out cooperative
projects in petroleum and petrochemical industries in accordance
with laws of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ratwatte said at the signing ceremony that though the two
countries have had a long history of friendship, this is the first
time that they have come to an agreement connected with the
petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the two sides will have a pleasant cooperation in
future.
</P>
<P>
Gu, on her part, said she will instruct related departments of
her ministry to set up working teams in accordance with the terms
of the MOU and carry out feasibility studies soon.
</P>
<P>
Gu arrived here on January 2 at the invitation of President
Chandrika Kumaratunga and Minister Ratwatte.
</P>
</TEXT>
