<HEADLINE> India to Host Global Meeting on Coal in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- India is to host the
first-ever international conference here this month to discuss
coal and coal-related issues, Coal Ministry officials said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The conference, scheduled for January 12 and 13, will provide
an opportunity to coal producers, power utilities, other users of
coal, technology suppliers, equipment manufacturers and financial
institutions to exchange views on some of the topical issues.
</P>
<P>
The issues to be deliberated include the latest technologies of
coal washing as available in India and the rest of the world,
environmental and other economic benefits of the use of washed
coal, government policy and the role of the private sector in the
development of washeries.
</P>
<P>
India's coal reserves are estimated at 203 billion tons, of
which over 85 percent is of inferior quality, with an ash content
of up to 45 percent and sometimes as high as 50 percent or more,
the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
