<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Credit for Vietnam's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved a 35 million U.S. dollar credit to support commercial
debt and debt service reduction operations in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The project will help finance Vietnam's Debt and Debt-Service
Reduction (DDSR) agreement with its London Club creditors.
</P>
<P>
The credit, which is provided by the International Development
Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary lending wing for
developing countries, will finance a portion of the costs of the
DDSR Agreement signed on December 16, 1997.
</P>
<P>
This agreement will deliver substantial debt relief and yield a
sustainable debt service. The project will also help Vietnam
settle all its outstanding private, uninsured commercial arrears,
totaling 797 million dollars. The step will remove a major
impediment to Vietnam's access to international capital markets,
particularly to trade credits.
</P>
<P>
The project will also facilitate private sector involvement in
the financing of critical infrastructure, thereby strengthening
the country's medium-and-long-term growth prospects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
