<HEADLINE> China's Light Industry Sets Sights on Foreign Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry need to
boost exports and attract more foreign capital and technology this
year, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Exports should increase by over six percent, the newspaper
quoted Yu Zhen, chairwoman of the China National Council of Light
Industry, as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to her, the export target of light industrial
products is set at 58 billion U.S. dollars this year, comparing
with 34.8 billion U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
To reach that goal, the light industrial sector should focus on
developing more overseas markets in Asia, Africa, Latin America,
Eastern Europe and the other nations of the Commonwealth of the
Independent States in the year of 1998, said Yu.
</P>
<P>
She noted the importance of expanding markets in the Middle
East, which is abundant in natural resources but lacks daily
necessities.
</P>
<P>
Light industrial enterprises are also urged to cooperate via
multiple channels with foreign companies by actively participating
in international shows and exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
Yu emphasized that quality is the key in establishing the
reputation of China's light industry at domestic and overseas
markets.
</P>
<P>
The chairperson urged light industrial enterprises to make
greater efforts to improve quality and technological content of
traditional labor-intensive exports and to improve the proportion
of capital-intensive machinery and electronics in overall exports,
as well as encouraged light industrial enterprises to expand
business overseas.
</P>
<P>
She added China's light industry expects to attract more
foreign capital and technology this year as China will give tariff
exemption to imported technologies and equipment China can not
produce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
