<HEADLINE> Hebei Pledges to Deal Harshly With Pornography </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province
dealt harshly with publishers of pornography and individuals
involved in pirating audio and visual porno materials over the
past year, with authorities confiscating over 50 kinds of audio
and visual publications and more than 120 related titles of books
and magazines.
</P>
<P>
The public security bureau has completed investigations of 210
related cases.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the province, which is located in the middle reaches
of the Yangtze River, forced the closure of the country's largest
illegal publications market -- the "Wusheng Road Cultural
Market". Hubei also closed two illegal CD production lines
operating in a shipyard.
</P>
<P>
The new market for legal products, produced mainly state-owned
enterprises, opened in mid-December and has since witnessed
booming business.  
</P>
