<HEADLINE> Venezuela's Oil Prices Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Export prices of Venezuelan oil
reduced 33 cents per barrel this week, the Power and Mining
Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The price dropped from 13.88 U.S. dollars per barrel on
December 31 to 13.55 dollars Monday.
</P>
<P>
Energy experts said that if the price continued declining in
the first quarter of 1998, the situation would be worse for the
rest of the year.
</P>
<P>
Specialists said the reduction in price resulted from forecasts
of a gentle winter in the United States, an excessive supply from
the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries, the resumption
of Iraq's exports and financial turmoil of Southeastern Asian
countries. 
</P>
