<HEADLINE> Cuba Expects to Improve Tourism In 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Tourism industry in Cuba expects
to host 1.43 million foreign visitors this year, earning foreign
currency for over one billion U.S. dollars, governmental sources
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government expects to invest 20 percent more than the
previous year in tourism infrastructure, which include the
construction of 1,800 more rooms and to improve the already
existing state-run hotels with some 4,000 rooms.
</P>
<P>
The government will disburse 80 million dollars ton increase
the national products presence in the industry.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Cuba welcomed some 1.17 million foreign visitors,
16.5 percent more than a the year before and net profits made
almost 850 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Most of the tourists that traveled to Cuba last year were
Italian, followed by canadians, Spaniards, Germans and
Mexicans.
</P>
<P>
Governmental statistics show that there are 21 joint
ventures with private capitals in tourism with a
private investment of more than 667 million dollars and a
capacity of 2,500 rooms, which makes up 9.3 percent of the total
nationwide. 
</P>
