<HEADLINE> More Events to be Added for World Short-Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 7 (Xinhua) -- More sprint races will be allowed
to compete at the world short-course swimming championships, the
International Amateur Swimming Federation (FINA) decided here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A FINA Congress agreed to add 50 meters backstroke,
breaststroke and butterfly and 100 meters individual medley to
both the men's and women's events.
</P>
<P>
The next world short-course championships are in Hong Kong in
April 1999. 
</P>
