<HEADLINE> Chile Domestic Air Flights Increase 28.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Domestic air flights in Chile
transported over 3.1 million people in 1997, 28.7 percent more
than 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Air authorities of Chile said Tuesday that
domestic air service enjoyed one of the largest increments in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Airlines of Chile takes the biggest share of the national
market with 42.1 percent, follows Ladeco, with 31.4 percent; and
National Airlines, with 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
Prospectives for domestic air flights for the year 2000 say
that about 9 million passengers could be flying through Chile,
five times as much as the figure registered in 1990. 
</P>
