<HEADLINE> Czech Koruna Bottoms at 35.5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Czech currency, the koruna,
hit a historic low of 35.5 against the United States dollar
Monday, the first day of new year trading.
</P>
<P>
The Czech currency also lowered against other major currencies
in the West as the Prague exchange market closed. The koruna
against German mark dropped to 19.53.
</P>
<P>
The koruna has lost 40 percent of its value against the
greenback when compared with its earlier 1997 level.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said political instability and an economic slide
accelerated the fall of the koruna against the dollar. 
</P>
