<HEADLINE> Xiamen Port Witnesses Increasing Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Xiamen Port in south China's
Fujian Province handled nearly 18 million tons of cargo in 1997,
up some 13 percent on the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Eleven million tons of the total involved foreign trade, a
substantial 25 percent rise on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The port handled 546,000 TEUs during 1997, up some 36 percent
on 1996.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises operating businesses in the port have
earned profits of more than 100 million yuan annually for three
consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The port operates five regularly scheduled international
shipping routes to Japan, Singapore, the Republic of Korea, the
United States and the Mediterranean.  
</P>
