<HEADLINE> Vicious Weather Knocks Out Power in Montreal, Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A prolonged and vicious winter
storm caused widespread power blackouts in Montreal and Ottawa
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Freezing rain wrecked havoc in Canada's second largest city of
Montreal, where power lines were weighed down by ice and sidewalks
turned into skating rinks.
</P>
<P>
More than 600,000 people were without power during much of the
day, according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
Schools in the Montreal area closed and some flights had to be
delayed or canceled.
</P>
<P>
In Ottawa, schools were still open, but a lot of students were
forced to stay at home because school buses were not running.
</P>
<P>
Numerous power failures were also reported throughout the
national capital region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
